Date: 1996-10-15

Title: Nambu-Goto string with massive ends at finite temperature

Authors: G. Lambiase and V.V. Nesterenko

Comments: LaTex file, 8 pages

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B398 (1997) 335-341

It is shown that the critical (or deconfinement) temperature for theNambu-Goto string connecting the point-like masses (quarks) does not depend onthe value of these masses. This temperature turns out to be the same as that inthe case of string with fixed ends (infinitely heavy immobile quarks).